if ("select".equals(el.normalName())) {
    Elements options = el.select("option[selected]");
    boolean added = false;
    for (Element option: options) {
        if (!added) {
            data.add(HttpConnection.KeyVal.create(name, option.val()));
            added = true;
        }
    }
    if (!added) {
        Element option = el.select("option").first();
        if (option != null)
            data.add(HttpConnection.KeyVal.create(name, option.val()));
    }
}
```

Only Add Last Selected Option
This solution involves iterating over the options in reverse order and adding the first selected option we encounter. This ensures that only the last selected option is added to the list for each select element.

```java
if ("select".equals(el.normalName())) {
    Elements options = el.select("option[selected]");
    for (int i = options.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        Element option = options.get(i);
        data.add(HttpConnection.KeyVal.create(name, option.val()));
        break;
    }
    if (options.size() == 0) {
        Element option = el.select("option").first();
        if (option != null)
            data.add(HttpConnection.KeyVal.create(name, option.val()));
    }
}
```

